# Documentation Guidelines

## Documentation Structure

The project documentation is built with Astro and located in [docs/](mdc:docs/):

- **[docs/src/content/docs/](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/)** - Main documentation content
- **[docs/src/content/docs/guides/](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/guides/)** - User guides
- **[docs/astro.config.mjs](mdc:docs/astro.config.mjs)** - Astro configuration
- **[docs/package.json](mdc:docs/package.json)** - Documentation dependencies

## Documentation Content

- **API Reference**: [docs/src/content/docs/api.mdx](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/api.mdx)
- **CLI Usage**: [docs/src/content/docs/cli.mdx](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/cli.mdx)
- **Configuration**: [docs/src/content/docs/configuration.mdx](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/configuration.mdx)
- **Core Concepts**: [docs/src/content/docs/core.mdx](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/core.mdx)
- **Security**: [docs/src/content/docs/guides/security.mdx](mdc:docs/src/content/docs/guides/security.mdx)

## Writing Documentation

- Use Markdown (.mdx) format for all documentation
- Include code examples with proper syntax highlighting
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes
- Use clear, concise language
- Include security considerations where relevant

## Code Documentation

- Use Rust doc comments (`///`) for public APIs
- Include examples in doc comments
- Document error conditions and edge cases
- Use `cargo doc` to generate API documentation

## README Files

- **[README.md](mdc:README.md)** - Project overview and quick start
- **[docs/README.md](mdc:docs/README.md)** - Documentation setup and build instructions

## Building Documentation

- Documentation uses Astro static site generator
- Run `bun install` in docs directory to install dependencies
- Use `bun run dev` to start development server
- Use `bun run build` to build static site
